    "rationale": "This example demonstrates the selective oxidation of a sterically hindered secondary alcohol (1-cyclohexyl-2,2-dimethyl-1-propanol) to the corresponding ketone (1-cyclohexyl-2,2-dimethyl-1-propanone) under Swern conditions. The presence of the bulky tert-butyl and cyclohexyl groups makes this a specific and non-trivial example, clearly illustrating the reaction's utility for converting secondary alcohols to ketones without over-oxidation or side reactions on the aliphatic rings.",
    "collision_avoidance_note": "The substrate contains both a cyclohexyl and a tert-butyl group attached to the carbinol carbon, creating a distinct and sterically demanding environment. This specific combination of bulky aliphatic groups is designed to be unique and avoid trivial matches with simple alcohol oxidations, ensuring it serves as a precise seed for the Swern oxidation family.",
